// Maximum number of child boxes generated per container
#define MAX_CHILD_BOXES 25
#define MAX_CHILD_BOXES_SMALL 8
#define MAX_PADDING 4

//------------------------------------------------
//--- 010 Editor v8.0 Binary Template
//
//      File: MP4_complete.bt
//   Authors: Extended from Alexey Lyashko, Andrew Molyneux, Marian Denes, SweetScape, Marko Musa
//   Version: 4.0
//   Purpose: Comprehensive template for parsing MP4/MOV/M4V/M4A files.
//            Covers all ISO 14496-12/14/15 box types including:
//            fragmented MP4, HEIF, DRM/CENC, Dolby Vision, AV1, HEVC,
//            Opus, FLAC, AC-3/EC-3, AC-4, DTS, WebVTT, TTML, and more.
//  Category: Video
// File Mask: *.mp4,*.mov,*.m4v,*.m4a,*.3gp,*.heic,*.heif,*.avif
//  ID Bytes: [+4] 66 74 79 70, [+4] 6D 6F 6F 76, [+4] 6D 64 61 74
//   History:
//   4.0   2025-03-10 Full coverage of ISO BMFF box types from JSON spec.
//   3.3   2019-08-08 M. Musa: Modified box logic to respect box size in header.
//   3.2   2019-02-03 A. Lyashko: Added support for fragmented MP4 files.
//   3.1   2018-06-17 A. Lyashko: Added support for sample table atoms.
//   3.0   2017-10-03 A Molyneux: Total rewrite, more complete and robust.
//------------------------------------------------

BigEndian();

